OL,4,Creveal extent of violence against NHS
OL,5,Cstaff
OL,7,FJames Wilkie, who was appointed
OL,8,FChairman in August 2024, said the
OL,9,Fnumber of incidents was 'a lot' and
OL,10,Fquestioned whether other hospital
OL,11,Ftrusts had the same number of
OL,12,Fincidents happening to their staff.
OL,14,FHe asked, "Are the approaches we have
OL,15,Fgot in place satisfactory because this
OL,16,Fis something we really need to have
OL,17,Fzero tolerance on in terms of our
OL,18,Fcommitment to the staff who work for
OL,19,Fus in very difficult circumstances on
OL,20,Foccasion?"
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
